          "content_excerpt": "Summary\n\nThis week was a strong step forward for the Mobile App Launch (MOB).\n\nKey wins\n- Performance: We saw roughly a 15% improvement in cold-start time on mid-tier Android devices after the latest round of optimizations.\n- Growth: Early access cohort grew by ~10% week-over-week as we expanded the invite pool and reduced sign-up friction.\n- Stability: Crash-free sessions are holding steady above our target threshold despite the new feature work.\n\nDetails\n\n1. Performance improvements (~15%)\nSam and Jordan landed the initial batch of optimizations on the feed rendering path. In synthetic benchmarks, cold-start time improved by ~15% compared to last week’s baseline. We’ll keep an eye on real-world telemetry over the next few days to confirm the gains hold at scale.\n\n2. User growth (~10% WoW)\nTop of funnel metrics for the early access program show ~10% week-over-week growth in activated users. The largest contributors appear to be:\n- Smoother onboarding in the latest build\n- Targeted outreach to high-intent users from the waitlist\n\nNext week\n- Lock the plan for the 11/10 Planning milestone and finalize scope for the next development phase.\n- Validate performance gains on lower-end devices and in less reliable network conditions.\n- Align with Engineering on remaining risk areas before we commit to the 11/30 launch date."
